node.title: Emergency response continues in Sydney after freak storm explodes on city
node.description: Thousands remain without power and roads are closed.
node.content: ["Parts of Sydney are in clean-up mode after a freak storm exploded on the city's Northern Beaches.", "It came out of nowhere and was deadly and damaging.\u00a0", "On Sunday night, Mother Nature took a ferocious and violent turn as a freak storm slammed into Sydney's northern beaches.", "It was quick, chaotic and destructive, leaving trees toppled and cars crushed. Corrugated iron was found metres from homes as they were stripped bare.", "Three women were in the wrong place at the wrong time. One was killed, her two friends were seriously injured by a falling tree.", "Others are lucky to be alive. A falling tree missed one man by just 40 seconds.", "\"I was 40 seconds away from dying, that's hit me when I got home,\" he says. \"I didn't sleep much last night.\"", "His house and the neighbourhoods surrounding it are littered with damage on Monday.", "The emergency response is continuing as thousands remain without power and roads are closed.\u00a0", "Residents are helping with the cleanup, all able to recall exactly where they were and what they were doing when terror struck.", "It's an afternoon no one wants to relive. But forecasters are predicting more storms - a characteristic of Australia's summer devil that they call La Ni\u00f1a.\u00a0\u00a0"]
